That part which until 1.4.1934 formed part of the parish of 
    Alfreton. See also Table 2, note (j).

Abolished 1.4.1974 and added to the Gedling unparished area. See also Table 
    2, note (o).

Only that part of the unparished area which until 1.4.1974 formed the parish of Hucknall Torkard. 
    See also Table 2, note (y).

Created 1894 out of the parish of Nuthall. See also Table 2, note 
    (y).

Abolished 1.4.1899 and added to the parish of Nottingham. 
    See also Table 2, note (i).

Abolished 1.4.1935 and divided between the parishes of Beeston 
    & Stapleford and Nottingham. See also Table 2, note (o).

Created 1.4.1935 out of the parishes of Beeston, Stalpeford, Chilwell, 
    Bramcote and Toton. Abolished 1.4.1974 to become the Broxtowe unparished area. See also Table 
    2, note (r).

Renamed 28.9.1977 to become the parish of Bestwood St. Albans. 
    See also Table 2, notes (b) and (o).

Created 28.9.1977 by renaming the parish of Bestwood Park. See 
    also Table 2, note (y).

Abolished 1.4.1933 and added to the parish of Nottingham. 
    See also Table 2, note (o).

Created 1.4.1896 out of the parish of Greasley. See also Table 
    2, note (y).

Unparished area which until 1.4.1974 formed the parish of Beeston & Stapleford. See also Table 2, note 
    (y).

Abolished 1.4.1899 and added to the parish of Nottingham. 
    See also Table 2, note (i).

Abolished 1.4.1974 and added to the Gedling unparished 
    area. See also Table 2, note (e).

Abolished 1.4.1952 and divided between the parishes of Nottingham, 
    Beeston & Stapleford and Barton in Fabis. See also Table 2, notes (r) and 
    (s).

Abolished 1.4.1934 and divided between the parishes of Alfreton 
    and Codnor & Loscoe. See also Table 2, note (j).

Abolished 1.4.1935 and divided between the parishes of Carlton 
    and Holme Pierrepont. See also Table 2, notes (k) and (o).

Created 1.4.1980 out of the Gedling unparished area. See also 
    Table 2, note (y).
Abolished 1.4.1935 and added to the parish of Carlton.

Unparished area which until 1.4.1974 formed the parishes of 
    Arnold and Carlton. See also Table 2, note (y).

That part which until 1.4.1935 formed part of the parish of 
    Colwick. See also Table 2, note (k).
Abolished 1.4.1974 and added to the Ashfield unparished area.

Created 1.4.1896 out of the parish of Greasley. See also Table 
    2, note (y).

Abolished 1.4.1974 to become an unparished area. See also Table 
    2, notes (g), (h) and (u).

Created 1894 from the part of the parish of Wilford in Nottingham 
    County Borough. Abolished 1.4.1899 and added to the parish of Nottingham. 
    See also Table 2, note (i).

That part which until 1.4.1899 formed the parishes of Basford, 
    Bulwell and North Wilford. See also Table 2, note (i).

That part which until 1.4.1933 formed the parishes of 
    Bilborough and Wollaton and parts of the parishes of Arnold, Beeston, 
    Bestwood Park and Colwick. See also Table 2, note (o).

Abolished 1.4.1974 and added to the Nottingham unparished area. 
    See also Table 2, notes (p) and (v).

That part which until 30.9.1895 formed part of the parish of 
    Kirkby in Ashfield. See also Table 2, note (g).

Created 1.4.1987 out of the parishes of Blidworth and 
    Newstead. See also Table 2, notes (x) and (y).

Created 1894 out of the rural parts of the parishes of Wilford 
    and Lenton. Abolished 1.4.1935 and added to the parish of West Bridgford. 
    See also Table 2, note (f).

That part which until 1894 formed the parts of the 
    parishes of Carlton and West Bridgford in Nottingham county borough. See 
    also Table 2, note (e).

Created 1.4.1987 out of the Broxtowe unparished area. See also Table 2, note 
    (y).

Abolished 1.4.1974 to become the Rushcliffe unparished area. See also Table 
    2, notes (d), (e), (l), (s), (t) and (w).

Abolished 1894 and divided between the parishes of North Wilford 
    and South Wilford.

Abolished 1.4.1933 and added to the parish of Nottingham. 
    See also Table 2, note (o).
